After marriage, women in Fiji are often “beaten into submission” because they cannot give birth to a “male heir.”

Brenda Myers-Powell is a mother of ten. She “work[ed] the streets” and abused drugs before she joined the Sex Workers Outreach Project Chicago. This intervention helped her leave the life behind and become a doula. She advocated the legalization of sex work, noting the “…health and safety” she’d harm herself to promote through social work. Her exact words are “No more dying in John’s cars and basements. No more living in shelters we are prostitutes now who go by a different name.” She gave a remarkably thought out address to the United Nations that you can view here.

If people knew about the crimes men commit against their family abroad, could they support the military aid that brings Islamists to power in an ever-expanding region? Or, would they concede the Afghan civilian casualties are just collateral damage in the War on Terror?
